result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt: Transcript received and filed for the following date and event: July 13, 2022 Plea and Sentencing hearing filed by Court Reporter Cheryl Humpal.
SEE MINUTES FROM THE 07/13/2022 Plea/Sentencing Hearing.

03:17 PM; Case called for Review hearing and Plea/sentencing hearing.  Defendant Corbin T Zebrasky in court, in custody at WCJ, with attorney Joseph F Owens.  Jack A. Pitzo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court will first address the NGI report filed by Dr. Westendorf back on 05/23/2022.  Atty. Pitzo maintains he is in agreement with Dr. Westendorf's findings.  Atty. Owens advises he has been able to review the report with his client and there are no objections to Dr. Westendorf's findings.  As a result Atty. Owens withdraws his previous NGI plea and will proceed to plea and sentencing today.  Court will accept the findings in Dr. Westendorf's report and will accept Atty. Owens' withdraw of the NGI plea.  Court will now proceed to plea and sentencing.

State recites the offer.  Atty. Owens confirms the offer.  Pursuant to the offer the Court will order this case dismissed and read into 21CF953 & 21CF1553.

Plea/sentencing hearing on July 13, 2022 at 02:30 pm.
Review hearing on July 13, 2022 at 02:30 pm.

01:40 PM; Case called for Review hearing.  Defendant Corbin T Zebrasky in court, in custody, with attorney Joseph F Owens.   Charles Patrick Hoffmann appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court confirms with counsel they have received and reviewed Dr. Westendorf's NGI report.  State has reviewed the report and does not object to Dr. Westendorf's findings.  Atty. Owens has reviewed the report but advises his client has not had a opportunity to review the report, as a result he cannot say for sure that his client is in agreement with the findings.  Atty. Owens is requesting another further proceedings date to allow him time to review the report with his client and continue negotiations with the State to resolve all the matters.  Court adjourns for continued review hearing and projected plea and sentencing hearing.  Review hearing scheduled for July 13, 2022 at 02:30 pm.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for July 13, 2022 at 02:30 pm.

Invoice and Affidavit  for services provided by Dr. Westendorf.  ** Reviewed by Judge Lau on 5/24/22 - Approved.** 

*Forwarded to Yvonne for payment* (am)
2nd NGI Evaluation report filed by Dr. Westendorf.
Review hearing on June 1, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Order for 2nd Examination under 971.16 Wis. Stats. (Not Guilty by Reason of Mental Disease or Defect) signed by Judge Laura Lau 04/06/2022.  2nd Examination to be performed by Dr. Melissa Westendorf with report due by 05/23/2022.
Review hearing on May 23, 2022 at 03:00 pm.

10:51 AM; Case called for Review hearing.  Defendant Corbin T Zebrasky in court, in custody, with attorney Joseph F Owens.   Jack A. Pitzo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reviews the case on the record and notes defense may want an independant evaluation.  Court inquires how the matter will be proceeding today.  Atty. Owens first notes it has filed a motion to modify bail in 21CF1553 only, as well, a report from Anthony Hale is attached with regards to his evaluation of the defendant.  Atty. Owens outlines the findings in the report on the record, and he believes the defendant should undergo another evaluation by a psychiatrist.  Atty. Owens presents additional statements; he needs some additional time to have another psychiatrist evaluate his client.  Atty. Pitzo presents statements; he notes the only other option at this point for defense is to request another NGI examination and if that is being requested today he has no objection. The Court will grant the defendant's request for a 2nd NGI evaluation under Wis. Stats. 971.16.  The court will appoint Dr. Westendorf to conduct the 2nd NGI evaluation.  Court will adjourn for 45 days for review of that 2nd evaluation.  Court will also hold in abeyance Atty. Owens' motion to modify bail in 21CF1553 and address at a later date.  Review hearing scheduled for May 23, 2022 at 03:00 pm.
Review hearing on April 6, 2022 at 10:30 am.

09:16 AM Defendant Corbin T Zebrasky in court, in custody, with attorney Joseph F Owens.  District Attorney's Office Law Intern, Katrina Voge, appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court addresses Arraginment in 22CM37 and 22CM38.  Defense enters a not guilty by reason of mental disease or defect plea.  Both counsel have received and reviewed the doctor's report.  State is not contesting the findings of the report.  Defense objects to the conclustion of the reports and requests time to have additional experts review the material and provide reports.  Review hearing scheduled for April 6, 2022 at 10:30 am.
Arraignment on January 28, 2022 at 09:00 am.
Motion and Order To Seal Victim/Witness Identification Key signed by Judge Lau.

Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing.  Defendant to have no contact with Victim A listed in the Criminal Complaint/Victim Identification Key.  Defendant is not to share, reproduce or distribute any personal and/or identifying information about the crime victim(s), except to their attorney.

01:09 PM Defendant Corbin T Zebrasky in court, in custody.  Andrew Nesheim appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reads Criminal Complaint to the defendant on the record.  Service admitted/advised of charges and potential penalties.  Court advises of right to an attorney.  The Court will not enter a plea at this time and set this matter before the Trial Court as the defendant is currently pending on additional cases that are set for a review hearing.  Arraignment scheduled for January 28, 2022 at 09:00 am.
